reviews.title: One of the best fried fish we have ever had!
reviews.text: We arrived at this place after reading several recommendations (we made a road trip throughout the Netherlands) and were amazed by the fresh and tasty portions. The staff was really friendly although didn't speak English that good. Definitely recommended!

reviews.title: Best fish shop
reviews.text:
Every friday i go there to buy fish. Mostly baked fish but also smoked and fresh fish.

Higly recommended!

reviews.title: couleur locale in fishmongers
reviews.text: This review needs some explanation. It is very good, but not because you will be sitting on velvet chairs in a luxurious environment. No, if you can sit, it will be in old chairs outside underneath a plastic raincover 'roof' that is attached to the makeshift container like building in which the 'boys Van de Fant' sell their fish, fried or fresh. What they sell tastes good and the boys are so popular, cars come and go constantly. Locals go here. So, that's why this is a very good place.

reviews.title: Daily fresh fish
reviews.text: This place is more a kind of takeaway than a restaurant. It has got a few chairs andd a table. But the fish is super. They smoke the fish in the back of the place. The smoked mackerel was the best we tasted ever. The haring was deliciously greasy. We also liked the battered fish - crispy and tasty. The meat was excellent (moist, not dry) and with lovely taste (the right amount and kind of spices). On monday they don't serve fresh fish because there is no catch in the weekend. All is super fresh. We loved it.

reviews.title: Great fish fastfood
reviews.text: I tried everything on the menu. from raw hering, slamon tartar  to fried...  in one lunch. that is a very good place to go, relax, qualitative and not complicated... fried no garnish! recommand

reviews.title: Amazing!
reviews.text: fresh fish with a good price. If you go to Urk, you certainly need to check this one out. the quality of the sea food as perfectly high and I would for sure recommend it.
